The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Formidables in the lead
                                                                                                                       7                                      Formidables in the lead
            A CORRESPONDENT                      
	Calcutta: The 52nd Winter National Bridge Championships, being held for the fourth time in the city, has drawn a record number of entries for the team events. The newly-introduced Ruia Silver Teams got an incredible 95 entries whereas the Ruia Gold received 81 entries.         
	In the Ruia Gold after five rounds, the Formidables are leading the pack with 110 VPs followed by P R Ghosh-IV (107 VPs), Poddar Developers from Mumbai, Maharaja B, Baneet and winners of the recent 3rd Commonwealth Bridge Championships, Hemant Jalan.         
	In the Ruia Silver Dipak Mitras-IV are in the lead after five rounds with 102 VPs followed by Srikanto-IV 99 VPs. At 98 VPs are Patni, A. K. Upadhaya, Padhi Bhubaneswar and Chinchak.         
	On Sunday, the Ruia Gold and Silver will have 6 amp; 8 rounds respectively to qualify 24 teams in the Ruia Gold and 10 teams in the Ruia Silver.         
	Close to 200 teams are participating in a Winter National, which is a record in recent times. The Ruia Silver allows players below the category of masters to play at their level making it absorbing and competitive for all levels of players. Two masters can play on the Silver Team but not with each other.         
	For the first time in the history of the Winter Nationals, a huge prize money is being offered along with the silverware. With the newly formatted events players can play more events for more number of days than in the previous nationals.         
	This meet, organised by West Bengal Bridge Association, also includes the Holkar Pairs, the IMP Pairs, the Categorised Pairs and the Mixed Pairs.                                                                                                                     
